The paper discusses modeling neural networks as Gaussian processes, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the distribution of outputs and the behavior of neural networks, which are topics related to neural networks and their applications, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the decay of higher order terms, which is a topic related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the perturbation of the Gaussian process under training, which is a topic related to systems and control, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
